# services/ledger is a colocated but INDEPENDENT domain tenant.
#
# It carries its own go.mod, go.work, third_party/tessera submodule, CI
# (.github/workflows/ledger-*.yml), and container image
# (ghcr.io/baseproof/tooling/ledger). The tooling monorepo
# layering laws — scripts/dependency-law.sh and scripts/client-contract.sh —
# govern the AGNOSTIC HALF: libs/ and the first-party services (auditor,
# witness). They do NOT govern this tenant; the ledger lives in-tree for
# colocation only and is validated by its own pipeline.
#
# This marker is the mechanism: scripts/lib/governed.sh prunes any subtree
# carrying a .law-exempt file from the law's scans. The ledger nonetheless
# remains a FORBIDDEN import target for the agnostic half — DOMAIN_RE in
# dependency-law.sh names it at both its old (clearcompass-ai/ledger) and new
# (baseproof/tooling/services/ledger) module paths.
